Hex Keys is an Isomorphic MIDI keyboard with a USB device interface. The case and keys were cut on a Laser Cutter and the electronics built on strip board.
 
Published in The MagPi Magazine #109 September 2021.
With an Isomorphic keyboard the pattern of notes to play any chord is the same for any key, making it much easier to learn.

Part 2 shows the full working system.
Here you will find the software to make it run. 

As Fig 3 was not shown fully in the Magazine layout we have added it to this folder.


